# =============================================================================
# .trivyignore — ARGUS sandbox image vulnerability allowlist
# Owner: ARGUS supply-chain (ARG-034, Cycle 4)
# Last reviewed: 2026-04-20
#
# This file curates the **only** known-acceptable CVEs that block-mode Trivy
# (severity=CRITICAL,HIGH; ignore-unfixed=false) is permitted to suppress
# during the .github/workflows/sandbox-images.yml :: trivy-scan job.
#
# Policy (enforced by docs/sandbox-images.md §3 and code review):
#
#   1. Empty by default.
#      A clean Kali-rolling base SHOULD pass blocking Trivy. Only add an
#      entry after a real scan flags a CVE that is demonstrably non-
#      exploitable in the ARGUS sandbox runtime — never preemptively.
#
#   2. Every entry MUST be on its own line and MUST be immediately preceded
#      by a comment block carrying:
#        - CVE-YYYY-NNNNN identifier (matches the entry below).
#        - Justification: why this CVE is non-applicable to ARGUS.
#          Concretely: which package, which feature path, why the sandbox
#          never reaches it. Do NOT write "false positive" without proof.
#        - Owner: ARG-NNN that added the entry.
#        - Expiry: YYYY-MM-DD (90 days from the date the entry was added).
#          On expiry, the cycle owner MUST re-evaluate: either remove the
#          entry (CVE has a fix and we now upgrade) or refresh the
#          justification (still non-applicable, push expiry +90d) and the
#          reviewer signature.
#
#      Format (use exactly this template):
#
#        # CVE-YYYY-NNNNN — vulnerability in <package> only triggered when used as <feature>;
#        # ARGUS sandbox does not invoke this feature (evidence: <path/file or test>).
#        # Owner: ARG-NNN; reviewer: <handle>; expires: YYYY-MM-DD.
#        CVE-YYYY-NNNNN
#
#   3. NO blanket suppressions, ever.
#      No `**/*` patterns, no severity-level wildcards, no `--ignore-unfixed`
#      add-back. The CI workflow pins `ignore-unfixed: false` deliberately —
#      do not toggle it to mask CVEs.
#
#   4. Quarterly audit.
#      The Cycle owner runs:
#
#        grep -E '^CVE-[0-9]{4}-[0-9]+' .trivyignore
#
#      and confirms every active suppression has a non-expired comment block.
#      Expired entries surface in the audit report and either get removed
#      (preferred — upgrade the affected package) or re-justified.
#
# Sigstore Cosign attestation policy: every suppression is also recorded in
# the in-toto SLSA predicate produced by ARG-033 so downstream verifiers can
# audit the suppression set against the signed manifest.
#
# Local replay (regenerate the report off-CI):
#   trivy image --severity CRITICAL,HIGH --ignore-unfixed=false \
#               --exit-code 1 --ignorefile .trivyignore \
#               ghcr.io/<org>/argus-kali-web:<sha>
#
# =============================================================================
#
# ── Active suppressions (currently empty — first real scan will surface
# the actual list, see policy §1 above). Do NOT pre-populate.
#
